AGI - Russia has destroyed a historic building in Odessa known as the 'Harry Potter' Castle' with an Iskander missile loaded with cluster munitions. According to the Ukrainians it is evidence that the intention was to kill as many civilians as possible and in fact in the attack five people died and thirty others were wounded. >
&nbsp;
In addition to causing a fire that destroyed the castle's spire roof on the shores of the Black Sea in the tourist district of Arcadia the explosions of cluster munitions damaged other buildings in the area. "The attack was carried out with a ballistic missile Iskander with cluster munition in the head, > reads in a statement of the Ukrainian Procura, which adds that metal fragments and parts of the missile were found within a radius of 1.5 kilometers from the building belonging to a university foundation. Together with the statement, the Prosecutor distributed a video in which the explosions of the multiple submunions can be seen. The cluster ammunition is generally used to destroy more targets located within a certain distance from each other. This type of ammunition is usually used to hit formations of tanks or infantry and damage or put out combat the most armored vehicles or fighters scattered in a given area.
&nbsp;
According to the Odessa military expert, Alexander Kovalenko, this is the first time Russia uses cluster munitions against the city. "The idea of this type of ammunition is to hit a vast area, only that the blow was not directed against military targets but against civilian targets," he wrote on his social media.
